  "schema_version": "1.0",
  "type": "advisory",
  "official_name": "Advisory",
  "description": "Publications about vulnerabilities, incident reports, and safety publications — anything that documents 'something happened.'",
  "purpose": "Track and coordinate security and safety publications. Includes CVE records, vendor advisories (RHSA, DSA, MSRC), ecosystem databases (GHSA, OSV, RUSTSEC), AI vulnerability databases (AVID), and incident reports (AIID, NHTSA).",
  "format": "secid:advisory/<namespace>/<name>[#subpath]",
  "examples": [
    "secid:advisory/mitre.org/cve#CVE-2024-1234",
    "secid:advisory/nist.gov/nvd#CVE-2024-1234",
    "secid:advisory/github.com/advisories/ghsa#GHSA-jfh8-c2jp-5v3q",
    "secid:advisory/redhat.com/errata#RHSA-2024:1234",
    "secid:advisory/debian.org/dsa#DSA-5678-1"
  ],
  "notes": "Named 'advisory' not 'vulnerability' because a vulnerability doesn't exist without a publication describing it. Handles multi-vuln advisories (one RHSA can fix multiple CVEs). Incident reports share this type because they're structurally similar — publications documenting that something went wrong.",
